<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06296145 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06296145 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  OBITUARY; LOS-ANGELES; WOMAN; ARTS; COLLECTIBLE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Art patron Marcia Simon Weisman, who accumulated one of the nation's leadingcollections of contemporary art, has died after a massive stroke. She was 73.;  Mrs. Weisman died Saturday at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center, where she wastaken early last week after suffering the stroke, hospital spokesman Ron Wisesaid Monday.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  MARCIA SIMON WEISMAN, LEADING ART PATRON  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     She is survived by two sons, Richard and Daniel; a daughter, Nancy; twogranddaughters; and a sister and a brother. A memorial service was planned forthis morning at the Museum of Contemporary Art.;   Her devotion to placingfine art in public places brought more than 8,000 pieces to Cedars-Sinai,which hosts &quot;the largest collection of art in any hospital in the world,&quot; Wisesaid.;   &quot;The theory behind it is it provides both patients and visitors withan option to the usual magazine reading you come across in hospitals,&quot; Wisesaid. &quot;One could actually get a fairly thorough knowledge of modern art bycoming to Cedars.&quot;;   Mrs. Weisman's collection includes prints, sculpturesand paintings by artists ranging from Willem de Kooning to Andy Warhol.;   Shemarried businessman Frederick Weisman in 1938 and they began collecting in1952 after her husband left the employ of his brother-in-law, Norton Simon.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Los Angeles  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911022  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Tuesday  </DAY><MONTH>  October  </MONTH><PG.COL>  12B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  202  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Tuesday, October 22, 199100296145,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>